						<summary>

						<p>This records an agreement of the <hi rend="italic">Nāṭṭār</hi> (assembly) of Tiruviḷai-nāḍu to measure out once every year in their own place, 360 <hi rend="italic">kalam</hi> of paddy (to a representative of the temple) for the daily offerings to the deity (in their name) during the three services in the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
